      <h1>Online Demo</h1>

      Muvin has been applied to 3 distinct datasets:

      <ul class="w3-ul">
        <li><b>HAL (HAL Archives Ouvertes)</b> knowledge graph, which describes scientific publications from all research fields. HAL is maily used by French researchers, who systematically enrich the dataset by including their research ressources (e.g. articles, patents, reports, etc.). Using Muvin, the user can explore the scientific production of one or multiple researchers as well as their collaborations over time.<br>
          You can explore the data at <a href="/muvin/hal/" target="_blank" >http://dataviz.i3s.unice.fr/muvin/hal</a>
        </li>
        
        <li>The <b>CROBORA</b> dataset, which describes images (video thumbnails) extracted from videos used in the television during the last 20 years. Each image is annotated with descriptive keywords. Using Muvin, the user can explore the co-occurrence of those keywords, as well as understand the temporal evolution of their usage.<br>
          You can explore the data at <a href="/muvin/crobora/" target="_blank" >http://dataviz.i3s.unice.fr/muvin/crobora</a>
        </li>

        <li>The <b>Wasabi</b> knowledge graph, which describes popular songs. Using Muvin, the user can explore the discography of artists and collaborations between musical artists and groups across time. <br>
          You can explore the data at <a href="/muvin/wasabi/" target="_blank" >http://dataviz.i3s.unice.fr/muvin/wasabi</a><br><br>

          Using this dataset, we also provide a version of Muvin that uses audio to support user perception throughout the visual exploration process, and MIR analysis of songs through a direct link to the <a href="https://timeside.ircam.fr/docs/index.html">TimeSide service</a>. This version is available at <a href="http://dataviz.i3s.unice.fr/muvinWasabi/">http://dataviz.i3s.unice.fr/muvinWasabi/</a>
        </li>
      </ul>

      <p><b>Obs.:</b> We advice using Google Chrome with this tool, as some features might not work correctly on other browsers.</p>
